                         INSTALLING OpticsBenchUI 0.1

External packages needed prior to installation:

1) Graphical user interface is based on Qt 4.7.2 for Linux. Install it 
in dynamic linking mode (see documentation)
http://doc.qt.nokia.com/4.7/

2) Firewire Camera compliant with DCAM (IIDC) standard is based on libdc1394
http://damien.douxchamps.net/ieee1394/libdc1394/

3) Advantech boards are controlled via the advdaq library
http://support.advantech.com.tw/support/

4) HDF5 data library to manage data collection
http://www.hdfgroup.org/HDF5/

OpticsBenchUI is compiled within the Qt framework, using a requirement file called
OpticsBenchUI.pro. First you need to update OpticsBenchUI.pro according to 
libdc1394,advdaq,hdf5 libraries and include path installations (INCLUDEPATH, LIBS tags)

OpticsBenchUI installation steps:

In the source directory (where is present the OpticsBenchUI.pro file) do:

1) qmake OpticsBenchUI.pro

2) make

This will create an OpticsBenchUI executable

3) Set/Update the LD_LIBRARY_PATH environment variable with the library paths of 
libdc1394,advdaq,hdf5 libraries 

4) Launch OpticsBenchUI ! There is a documentation accessible from the GUI which 
will help you to configure the devices.
